      "text": "Superposition explains why individual neurons are hard to interpret."
    },
    "bridgeFrom": "From components, we look at the features they compute.",
    "intuition": {
      "analogy": "Packing luggage.",
      "analogyLimit": "Luggage has strict volume limits.",
      "text": "More features than dimensions -> non-orthogonal packing.\nWorks because features are sparse (rarely co-active).\nPolysemanticity: single neuron responds to multiple features because it sits on multiple feature directions."
